title: Water catchment wins environment grants to protect endangered button wrinklewort flower
text:
Water catchment wins environment gran... Water catchment wins environment grants to protect endangered button wrinklewort flower 8 hrs ago Read more: Sydney Morning Herald 
Molonglo Catchment Group president Karen Williams said the group received two grants: $34,000 to improve degraded land in the Lower Molonglo Nature Reserve, and $3945 to take care of a 2.3 hectare block next to the Chinese Embassy in Yarralumla. Ms Williams said the small Yarralumla block was home to probably one of the most significant populations of button wrinklewort flowers in Australia, and was also an Aboriginal cultural site where artefacts had been found.   Sydney Morning Herald.
